ξ 5.-ΤΗΕ RECONCILIATION or HERErrcs.

The question as to how far Christian initiation was valid when it was performed by an heretical sect had been a subject of discussion even before the close of the second century. Tertullian deals with it in his treatise on baptism, or, rather, he refers to the solution of the question which he had already given in a special book on the subject, drawn up in Greek.3 According 130 him, initiation performed by heretics separated from the Church has no validity.
